Polish Zloty Drops, Reverses Gains, on Global Growth Concern

-- B y   P i o t r   S k o l i m o w s k i
-- 
2011-08-18T09:31:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/polish-zloty-drops-reverses-gains-on-global-growth-concern.html
The Polish zloty declined, reversing
earlier gains, as stocks and U.S. futures fell on concerns
global economic growth will slow.  The zloty declined 0.2 percent to 4.1522 per euro at 11:27
a.m. in Warsaw.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Skolimowski in Warsaw at 
 pskolimowski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  